pageContext.claim: “You know, they were saying, but he didn't pass legislative bills. I think it's 38. And we're going to be talking about them, 38. ... And some of them are really big, having to do with regulation, having to do with lots of different things.”
pageContext.analysis: As of June 27, the president has signed 42 pieces of legislation but it is tough categorize them as "really big." Many work toward deregulation and dismantling Obamacare.
